% UTILITIES
%
% Files :
% cabc                         - cabc closes all open figures except the one in foreground (the current)
% cascade                      - cascade is a third party function used in FSDA demos and examples
% chkinputM                    - chkinputM makes some input parameters and user options checking
% chkinputR                    - chkinputR makes some input parameters and user options checking
% chkoptions                   - chkoptions checks whether all supplied options exist
% clickableMultiLegend         - clickableMultiLegend extends the clickableLegend by Ameya Deoras to figures with one legend for several subplots
% closereqFS                   - closereqFS is a user-defined close request function which displays a question dialog box
% dsxy2figxy                   - dsxy2figxy transforms points or positions from 'axes data units' to 'normalized figure units'
% eigs_sigma                   - eigs_sigma sets a non zero value for the optional parameter sigma of function eigs
% ellipse                      - ellipse generates an ellipse given mu (location vector) and Sigma (scatter matrix)
% FSColors                     - FScolors is a MATLAB class encapsulating some common color definitions  used in the FSDA toolbox. 
% FSMbonfbound                 - FSMbonfbound computes Bonferroni bounds for each step of the  search (in mult analysis)
% FSRbonfbound                 - FSRbonfbound computes Bonferroni bounds for each step of the search (in linear regression)
% ginputFS                     - ginputFS extends the MATLAB ginput to encounter specific FSDA interaction needs.
% logmvnpdfFS                  - logmvnpdfFS log of Multivariate normal probability density function (pdf)
% mahalFS                      - mahalFS computes Mahalanobis distances (in squared units) for each row of matrix Y 
% normBoxCox                   - normBoxCox computes normalized Box-Cox transformation
% position                     - position controls the position of the open figures
% ProgressBar                  - ProgressBar is a third party function called by FSDA functions using parallel computing
% quickselectFS                - quickselectFS finds the k-th order statistic
% rescale                      - rescale rescales numeric array to have specified minimum (a)  and maximum (b)
% selectdataFS                 - selectdataFS enables to select data points using the mouse, on scatter plot matrices or trajectories in the forward plots.
% setuphelp                    - Load appropriate HTML help documentation files depending on the installed version of MATLAB
% triu2vec                     - triu2vec extracts in a vector the linear indexes or the elements on and above the k-th diagonal of a square matrix
% upperfracpos                 - upperfracpos positions two figures on the upper part of the screen.
% waitforbuttonpressFS         - waitforbuttonpressFS produces a warning message when user closes the figure he is interacting with 
% zscoreFS                     - zscoresFS computes (robust) standardized z scores
